// Rule ids whose dedicated InvalidFiles fixture the validator does not reject
// as an error. Two cases: the check is not yet implemented in the local
// subset, or the rule is a best-practice recommendation (SHOULD) that emits at
// warning severity, so the fixture is not an error-match even though the check
// runs. The best-practice ontology rules (10511, 10528, 10529, 10706, 10707,
// 11905, 11907, 12007, 13505) are of the second kind; the conformance suite
// asserts their fail direction against the SBOL2_bp corpus instead. Kept
// explicit so the strict/loose match set is auditable and grows over time.
